con:testSuite.name: Facebook APIs
con:testSuite.con:description: The project demonstrates work with Virt which was created on the facebook API service basis https://graph.facebook.com

con:testCase.name: Post messages to the news feed (DataSource in Virt)
con:testCase.con:description: Before the Virt start, the needed service launch is carried out using Setup Script. Work with TestStep: DataSource, DataSource Loop, Properties, Property Transfer, Assertions, Groovy Script is demonstrated. The way the parameters can be transferred between the requests is shown. Upon completion, Virt is stopped with TearDown Script.

con:configuration.token: An active access token must be used to query information about the current user.

con:testStep.name: Get "id" from previous response to property

con:config.script: def response = context.expand( '${Post a news#Response#$.id}' ) context.getTestCase().getTestStepByName("Define properties").setPropertyValue("last_id", response)

con:testStep.name: Transfer properties from one request to other

con:testCase.con:setupScript: virtRunner.run("Virt_DataSource") context.getTestCase().getTestStepByName("Post a news over limit 2").setPropertyValue("access_token", "") context.getTestCase().getTestStepByName("Post a news over limit 2").setPropertyValue("message", "")

con:testCase.name: Filter the news feed (Assertions in Virt)
con:testCase.con:description: Before the Virt start, the needed service launch is carried out using Setup Script. Work with requests of REST type is demonstrated. Upon completion, Virt is stopped with TearDown Script.

con:testCase.name: Different dispatch strategies (in Virt)
con:testCase.con:description: Before the Virt start, the needed service launch is carried out using Setup Script. The way of working with Groovy Script and getting various response types to the requests over the same address is demonstrated. Upon completion, Virt is stopped with TearDown Script.

con:testStep.name: Groovy Script - Run request in a loop
